Package seng202.team4.controller

Class FlightPathTabController

  • java.lang.Object
    • seng202.team4.controller.DataController
      • seng202.team4.controller.FlightPathTabController
  • public class FlightPathTabController
extends DataController
    Performs logic for the 'Flight Path' tab of the application Responsible for connecting the flight path data to the JavaFX interface, this includes displaying the coordinates and altitude in the JavaFX TableView with data from the 'FlightPath' SQLite database table and also initialising/updating the additive filtering and searching of said data.

      • setTableData

        public void setTableData​(java.sql.ResultSet rs)
                  throws java.sql.SQLException
        Sets the JavaFX table with rows from the 'FlightPath' database table. This is done using the table query and assigning each record to a row in the table
        Specified by:
        setTableData in class DataController
        Parameters:
        rs - JDBC ResultSet obtained from querying the Database FlightPath table and is used to set the rows of the JavaFX data table by creating N FlightPath objects from the query that results in N tuples.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - if the query fails, throws an exception
